Ok I think I got it, it's way simpler than I thought:

```patch
diff --git a/crates/bevy_render/src/camera/projection.rs b/crates/bevy_render/src/camera/projection.rs
index 7deb061..c39fcf5 100644
--- a/crates/bevy_render/src/camera/projection.rs
+++ b/crates/bevy_render/src/camera/projection.rs
@@ -490,8 +490,8 @@ impl CameraProjection for OrthographicProjection {
             ScalingMode::Fixed { width, height } => (width, height),
         };

-        let origin_x = projection_width * self.viewport_origin.x;
-        let origin_y = projection_height * self.viewport_origin.y;
+        let origin_x = (projection_width * self.viewport_origin.x).round();
+        let origin_y = (projection_height * self.viewport_origin.y).round();

         self.area = Rect::new(
             self.scale * -origin_x,
```

No tearing or shifting this time ðŸ˜„ 

Hopefully, this won't cause any regressions somewhere else.
